text: Sabrina Kolker (born September 14, 1980) is a Canadian rower who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens and the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing. Kolker was born in Comox, Canada, and grew up in West Vancouver. She attended high school at Phillips Exeter Academy and then attended Stanford University. == References == Category:Canadian female rowers Category:Phillips Exeter Academy alumni Category:Tufts University alumni Category:Olympic rowers of Canada Category:Rowers at the 2004 Summer Olympics Category:Rowers at the 2008 Summer Olympics Category:1980 births Category:Living people
